OL,6,FHe continues: "You get up in the
OL,7,Fmorning to go to work and try and earn
OL,8,Fmoney as everyone else does, and money
OL,9,Fis really hard to earn at the moment.
OL,11,F"You have a lot of competition and
OL,12,Fthings like that, so you try and be
OL,13,Fcompetitive...to lose #2000 worth of
OL,14,Ftools and materials, it hits quite
OL,15,Fhard."
OL,17,FOne of his vans has now been fitted
OL,18,Fwith extra security and deadlocks on
OL,19,Feach door after it was burgled whilst
OL,20,Fon a job.
